COMMIT_BODY: Implements the hermeneutic profile schema per PROJECT.md §4.3.\n\nCovers all eight required axes: canon, text_base, authority_model,\ninterpretive_method, rule_of_faith, testament_relation, inspiration_model,\nand clarity_hierarchy. Each axis uses enums where options are well-defined\nwith escape hatches for tradition-specific positions.\n\nDesign decisions:\n- text_base is split into ot_primary/nt_primary with secondary consultations\n  and explicit variant positions for contested readings\n- interpretive_method is an ordered array (primary method first) since\n  traditions often layer multiple methods\n- rule_of_faith lists specific creeds/confessions as guardrails\n- clarity_hierarchy models both a general principle and specific\n  passage-priority rules for doctrinal tensions\n- version_history mirrors the pattern from claim.json\n- tradition field links profiles to their historical tradition\n\nThis is the second of four required schemas for Phase 0 exit.
NEXT_MODEL: google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview

